  "prompt": "What's it like to be a flight attendant?",
  "response": "Being a flight attendant can be an exciting but challenging job. Here are some key aspects:\n\nPros:\n- Travel opportunities and seeing different cities/countries\n- Meeting diverse people\n- Flexible schedule with extended time off between trips\n- Generally good pay and benefits\n- Exciting and dynamic work environment\n\nCons:\n- Irregular work hours and disrupted sleep schedules\n- Dealing with difficult passengers\n- Physical demands like standing for long periods\n- Time away from home and family\n- Jet lag and potential health challenges\n- High-stress situations during flights\n\nTypical responsibilities:\n- Passenger safety and comfort\n- Demonstrating safety procedures\n- Serving food and drinks\n- Handling emergencies\n- Managing passenger needs and conflicts\n- Performing pre-flight and post-flight duties\n\nRequirements typically include:\n- Customer service skills\n- Physical fitness\n- Height and weight restrictions\n- Language skills\n- Professional appearance\n- Ability to pass background checks and medical exams\n\nThe job requires patience, adaptability, and strong interpersonal skills. While glamorous in some ways, it's also hard work with significant challenges.",
